(A) Mel finished first
(B) Amy finished below Dan
(C) Eve finished last
(D) Dan finished either second or third
(E) Joe finished above Dan

The answer is (E).

(C) Joe finished second
(D) Eve finished second
(E) Dan finished second
model_outputs.model_answer:

Rob finished below Dan, so certainly Rob didn't finish second.
Amy and Eve can't have finished second, since they were sandwiched between Rob and Dan.
So, only Joe and Dan were left to finish second -- and we know that Joe did. This means that Dan must have finished either sixth or last. But since Dan was the only one listed among the five golfers, he can't have come in sixth, so he must have come in second.

Therefore, though (D) Eve finished second looks tempting, the correct answer is (C) Joe finished second.
